2
00:00:02.690 --> 00:00:04.650
What a day!

3
00:00:04.650 --> 00:00:05.860
It's gorgeous!

4
00:00:05.860 --> 00:00:09.950
As long as we can stay on this heading, we
should reach the Marine base in no time at all.

5
00:00:09.950 --> 00:00:12.200
[LUFFY]
Wow, Koby! You're great out here.

6
00:00:12.200 --> 00:00:15.290
You mean we're actually gonna reach
the place we originally set out for?

7
00:00:15.290 --> 00:00:16.620
[KOBY]
Of course. It's nothing.

8
00:00:16.620 --> 00:00:18.920
I'm just using the skills
that every sailor should have.

9
00:00:18.920 --> 00:00:20.420
[LUFFY laughing]

10
00:00:20.420 --> 00:00:22.840
You know, there's really
nothing to be so giggly about.

11
00:00:22.840 --> 00:00:25.380
Because... at the Marine Base...

12
00:00:25.380 --> 00:00:29.050
[sinister string music]

13
00:00:25.920 --> 00:00:28.090
they're holding
the great Pirate Hunter...

14
00:00:29.050 --> 00:00:31.340
Roronoa Zoro.

15
00:00:33.760 --> 00:00:35.890
[KOBY]
This is the man who's
diced up his bounties

16
00:00:35.890 --> 00:00:40.520
like an animal bent on carnage,
a blood-thirsty beast.

17
00:00:40.520 --> 00:00:45.360
He's been called nothing less than a living,
breathing demon in human form.

18
00:00:59.120 --> 00:01:01.250
Wealth, fame, power...

19
00:01:01.250 --> 00:01:05.420
Gold Roger, the King of the Pirates, obtained everything the world has to offer.

20
00:01:05.420 --> 00:01:09.260
What he said in his final moments drove countless souls to the seas.

21
00:01:09.260 --> 00:01:11.260
You want my treasure?

22
00:01:11.260 --> 00:01:13.050
Go ahead.

23
00:01:13.050 --> 00:01:14.260
Find it!

24
00:01:14.260 --> 00:01:16.850
Everything is right where I left it!

25
00:01:19.270 --> 00:01:23.980
People set their sights on the Grand Line in pursuit of their dreams.

26
00:01:23.980 --> 00:01:27.230
The world has truly entered the Great Pirate Era!

27
00:01:27.990 --> 00:01:33.240
Come aboard and bring along all your hopes and dreams

28
00:01:33.450 --> 00:01:39.040
I know together we'll find everything we're looking for

29
00:01:39.370 --> 00:01:40.290
One Piece!

30
00:01:45.500 --> 00:01:50.300
Compasses? Not for me. Left them all behind

31
00:01:51.180 --> 00:01:56.100
I'm headed out to sea, with my heart serving as guide

32
00:01:56.930 --> 00:02:02.140
Following the ancient map to the spot marked "X" reveals

33
00:02:02.140 --> 00:02:07.360
Yeah, it's only legendary till someone proves it's real

34
00:02:08.980 --> 00:02:11.310
When the world's got you down,

35
00:02:11.310 --> 00:02:14.450
lean on your crew, they'll turn it around

36
00:02:14.780 --> 00:02:19.790
Their biorhythm will carry you through

37
00:02:20.000 --> 00:02:21.830
We're gonna make the most of it

38
00:02:23.710 --> 00:02:29.000
Come aboard and bring along all your hopes and dreams

39
00:02:29.210 --> 00:02:34.590
I know together we'll find everything we're looking for

40
00:02:34.930 --> 00:02:37.640
Got some change to my name,

41
00:02:37.640 --> 00:02:40.850
and maybe you wanna be my friend?

42
00:02:41.140 --> 00:02:45.730
We are, we are on the cruise!

43
00:02:46.520 --> 00:02:47.360
WE ARE!

44
00:02:53.030 --> 00:02:54.400
We're here!

45
00:02:54.450 --> 00:02:58.200
<b>The Pirate King
and the Master Swordsman</b>

46
00:02:54.820 --> 00:02:56.990
The Marine base city!

47
00:02:58.200 --> 00:03:01.160
[whimsical orchestral music]

48
00:03:01.160 --> 00:03:03.040
Luffy, seriously,
you're out of your mind

49
00:03:03.040 --> 00:03:05.460
if you think the right thing to
do is get this guy to join you.

50
00:03:05.460 --> 00:03:07.290
Well, I haven't made up my mind yet.

51
00:03:07.290 --> 00:03:08.790
I gotta see if he's a good guy!

52
00:03:08.790 --> 00:03:10.960
He's imprisoned
because he's obviously not!

53
00:03:16.630 --> 00:03:18.890
[LUFFY]
Hey, is that guy Zoro
around here somewhere?

54
00:03:18.890 --> 00:03:19.180
[WOMAN gasps]

55
00:03:19.180 --> 00:03:20.350
[CROWD gasps]

56
00:03:20.930 --> 00:03:24.430
[CROWD whimpering]

57
00:03:24.430 --> 00:03:27.400
Maybe we shouldn't mention
the name "Zoro" here, okay?

58
00:03:28.310 --> 00:03:30.150
Let's head to the base
and check it out.

59
00:03:30.150 --> 00:03:32.150
You wanna be a Marine, right?

60
00:03:32.150 --> 00:03:35.610
Well, of course I do, Luffy,
but I really don't think I'm ready just yet.

61
00:03:35.610 --> 00:03:39.360
From what I've heard, the man in charge
of this base is named Captain Morgan.

62
00:03:39.360 --> 00:03:40.830
[CROWD gasps]

63
00:03:40.830 --> 00:03:44.160
[CROWD whimpering]

64
00:03:44.160 --> 00:03:45.790
[LUFFY laughs]

65
00:03:45.790 --> 00:03:47.580
This town is such a weird place.

66
00:03:47.580 --> 00:03:48.540
[KOBY]
That was odd.

67
00:03:48.540 --> 00:03:50.380
I mean, I understand if
they're scared of Zoro,

68
00:03:50.380 --> 00:03:52.920
but why did they flip when
I mentioned the Marine captain's name?

69
00:03:53.710 --> 00:03:56.840
I don't know. I've got
a bad feeling about this.

70
00:03:56.840 --> 00:03:59.340
[LUFFY]
Maybe they were all just jumpin'
around for the fun of it.

71
00:03:59.340 --> 00:04:00.930
And how would that make any sense?

72
00:04:02.760 --> 00:04:04.390
[LUFFY]
This looks like the place.

73
00:04:05.560 --> 00:04:06.890
I made it...

74
00:04:06.890 --> 00:04:08.310
[cries]

75
00:04:08.310 --> 00:04:10.650
This is where you
and I part ways, Luffy.

76
00:04:10.650 --> 00:04:12.730
We didn't have long together, but...

77
00:04:12.730 --> 00:04:13.270
[LUFFY grunts]

78
00:04:13.270 --> 00:04:14.320
Where's the foothold?

79
00:04:14.320 --> 00:04:15.400
[KOBY]
Get down from there!

80
00:04:15.400 --> 00:04:16.650
What're you doing?! They'll see you!

81
00:04:17.280 --> 00:04:19.360
Now where's this demon?

82
00:04:19.360 --> 00:04:21.030
[KOBY]
They wouldn't
keep him out in the open.

83
00:04:21.030 --> 00:04:23.740
He's probably tucked in
a prison cell below ground.

84
00:04:23.740 --> 00:04:24.950
[LUFFY]
There he is!

85
00:04:24.950 --> 00:04:26.200
I'm gonna get closer!

86
00:04:28.660 --> 00:04:30.120
Koby, look!

87
00:04:30.120 --> 00:04:31.040
[KOBY sighs]

88
00:04:31.040 --> 00:04:32.210
I'm telling you he's not–

89
00:04:32.210 --> 00:04:32.670
[gasp]

90
00:04:32.670 --> 00:04:37.840
[sinister orchestral music]

91
00:04:35.670 --> 00:04:42.510
<b>"Pirate Hunter" Roronoa Zoro</b>

92
00:04:37.840 --> 00:04:39.840
That hood on his head...

93
00:04:39.840 --> 00:04:41.510
and a haramaki...

94
00:04:42.510 --> 00:04:44.680
It's Roronoa Zoro!

95
00:04:46.390 --> 00:04:49.020
If we untie those ropes,
he can just walk away!

96
00:04:49.020 --> 00:04:51.270
Oh, don't be such an idiot, Luffy!

97
00:04:51.270 --> 00:04:54.110
There's no telling what a bandit
like him will do if you let him go!

98
00:04:54.110 --> 00:04:56.110
He might just kill us both!

99
00:04:56.110 --> 00:04:58.190
Don't worry, I'm strong.
I can protect us.

100
00:04:58.190 --> 00:05:00.660
[KOBY]
He's lost his mind!

101
00:05:00.660 --> 00:05:02.160
[ZORO]
Hey, you two!

102
00:05:02.160 --> 00:05:03.030
[KOBY screams]

103
00:05:04.200 --> 00:05:06.330
You're an eyesore.

104
00:05:08.160 --> 00:05:09.160
Get lost.

105
00:05:09.160 --> 00:05:10.540
[KOBY screams]

106
00:05:10.540 --> 00:05:14.210
Luffy, trust me, there's no chance you'll
survive with someone like him on your crew!

107
00:05:14.880 --> 00:05:16.500
[puzzling music]

108
00:05:16.500 --> 00:05:18.050
[RIKA]
Shh.

109
00:05:23.930 --> 00:05:24.470
[KOBY gasps]

110
00:05:24.470 --> 00:05:26.970
[KOBY yelps]
Luffy, we gotta stop her
or she'll be killed,

111
00:05:26.970 --> 00:05:29.060
either by the Marines
or the demon himself!

112
00:05:30.350 --> 00:05:31.020
[ZORO]
What do you want?

113
00:05:31.020 --> 00:05:33.100
I thought you might
be getting hungry now,

114
00:05:33.100 --> 00:05:34.560
so I made you
a couple of rice balls.

115
00:05:34.940 --> 00:05:36.820
[ZORO]
You got a death wish, kid?

116
00:05:36.820 --> 00:05:37.730
Just scram.

117
00:05:37.730 --> 00:05:40.400
[RIKA]
But you haven't eaten anything
the whole time you've been tied up.

118
00:05:40.400 --> 00:05:41.610
Here!

119
00:05:41.610 --> 00:05:44.120
I've never really made them before...

120
00:05:44.120 --> 00:05:46.330
but I did my best,
so I think they're fine.

121
00:05:47.370 --> 00:05:49.080
Listen, kid, I'm not hungry!

122
00:05:49.080 --> 00:05:51.540
Now stop irritating me,
and get outta here!

123
00:05:51.540 --> 00:05:52.000
[RIKA]
But–

124
00:05:52.000 --> 00:05:54.880
Do not make me kick
your ass, little girl!

125
00:05:54.880 --> 00:05:55.840
[HELMEPPO]
Now, now.

126
00:05:55.840 --> 00:05:57.380
No one likes a bully.

127
00:05:57.380 --> 00:05:58.210
[ZORO growls]

128
00:05:58.210 --> 00:06:00.260
[HELMEPPO chuckles] Roronoa Zoro,

129
00:05:58.800 --> 00:06:04.220
<b>Helmeppo
Captain Morgan's Son</b>

130
00:06:00.260 --> 00:06:02.760
you seem to be handling this well.

131
00:06:02.760 --> 00:06:04.220
Don't you agree?

132
00:06:04.220 --> 00:06:06.720
Hey, look. Now there's
another weird guy.

133
00:06:06.720 --> 00:06:07.850
That's great!

134
00:06:07.850 --> 00:06:09.560
He must be with the Marines.

135
00:06:09.560 --> 00:06:11.100
Now we know the girl will be safe.

136
00:06:11.730 --> 00:06:15.150
Looky, some tasty rice balls.

137
00:06:15.150 --> 00:06:16.900
[RIKA]
That's not for you!

138
00:06:17.900 --> 00:06:18.650
[HELMEPPO screams]

139
00:06:18.650 --> 00:06:19.400
Too sweet!

140
00:06:19.820 --> 00:06:21.490
They're packed with sugar!

141
00:06:21.490 --> 00:06:23.530
You're supposed to use
salt, you idiot! Salt!

142
00:06:23.530 --> 00:06:24.700
But I...

143
00:06:24.700 --> 00:06:26.660
I thought they'd taste better sweet.

144
00:06:26.660 --> 00:06:27.240
[HELMEPPO]
Gimme that!

145
00:06:27.240 --> 00:06:28.700
[HELMEPPO grunting]

146
00:06:28.700 --> 00:06:29.870
[RIKA]
No! Stop!

147
00:06:29.870 --> 00:06:32.120
[RIKA] I worked so hard!

148
00:06:30.290 --> 00:06:31.040
[KOBY gasps]

149
00:06:31.040 --> 00:06:32.120
That's just awful.

150
00:06:32.120 --> 00:06:33.710
[HELMEPPO grunts, sighs]

151
00:06:33.710 --> 00:06:37.460
[RIKA crying]

152
00:06:37.460 --> 00:06:38.710
But I...

153
00:06:38.710 --> 00:06:39.300
[sobs]

154
00:06:39.300 --> 00:06:41.550
worked so hard to make those...

155
00:06:41.550 --> 00:06:42.300
[sobs]

156
00:06:42.300 --> 00:06:43.590
Too bad...

157
00:06:43.590 --> 00:06:46.180
You must've not read
the notice that was posted.

